<typeStatus id="CB57B5B39203FFC4FCA1FE03EF1DFE0F" box="[813,861,400,423]" pageId="4" pageNumber="517">TYPE</typeStatus>
SPECIES. — 
<taxonomicName id="D3EC70929203FFC4FC5CFE03E8BAFE01" authority="Johnston, 1847" authorityName="Johnston" authorityYear="1847" box="[976,1274,400,424]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Flustridae" genus="Flustra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="4" pageNumber="517" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="coriacea">
<emphasis id="2698D7039203FFC4FC5CFE03E81FFE01" box="[976,1119,400,424]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="517">Flustra coriacea</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="707D76E09203FFC4FBE9FE03E8BAFE01" author="JOHNSTON G." box="[1125,1274,400,424]" pageId="4" pageNumber="517" refId="ref7546" refString="JOHNSTON G. 1847. - A History of the British Zoophytes. 2 nd ed. John van Voorst, London, 488 p. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 19627" type="book" year="1847">Johnston, 1847</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis id="2698D7039203FFC4FA8BFE02E96BFE01" box="[1287,1323,401,424]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="517">non</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="707D76E09203FFC4FAA3FE03E9E3FE01" author="ESPER E. J. C." box="[1327,1443,400,424]" pageId="4" pageNumber="517" refId="ref7272" refString="ESPER E. J. C. 1791 - 1797. - Forsetzungen der Pflanzenthiere in Abbildungen nach der Natur mit Farben erleuchtet hebst Beschreibungen Vol. Theil 1. Nurnberg, 230 p." type="book" year="1791">Esper, 1791</bibRefCitation>
), by monotypy; Recent, British Isles.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="5CF6589A9203FFC4FCA1FE64E877F987" pageId="4" pageNumber="517" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="14530B119203FFC4FCA1FE64EFD1FDB8" blockId="4.[811,1458,503,1582]" box="[813,913,503,529]" pageId="4" pageNumber="517">REMARKS</paragraph>
<paragraph id="14530B119203FFC4FCA1FD85E9D4FD59" blockId="4.[811,1458,503,1582]" pageId="4" pageNumber="517">
<bibRefCitation id="707D76E09203FFC4FCA1FD85EF8AFD98" author="GORDON D. P." box="[813,970,534,561]" pageId="4" pageNumber="517" pagination="1 - 198" refId="ref7435" refString="GORDON D. P. 1984. - The marine fauna of New Zealand: Bryozoa: Gymnolaemata from the Kermadec Ridge. New Zealand Oceanographic Institute Memoir 91: 1 - 198." type="journal article" year="1984">Gordon (1984)</bibRefCitation>
listed the key features of 
<taxonomicName id="D3EC70929203FFC4FB31FD84E963FD99" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1848" box="[1213,1315,535,560]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Microporidae" genus="Micropora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="4" pageNumber="517" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2698D7039203FFC4FB31FD84E963FD99" box="[1213,1315,535,560]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="517">Micropora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as its encrusting colony-form, raised lateral walls, granular cryptocyst that is minutely perforated and penetrated by opesiules close to the orifice, and basal pore chambers. Oral spines are rare, and ovicells are recumbent or immersed. In addition, the orifice is typically semielliptical in shape, and there is an avicularium located immediately distally of the orifice in most species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="14530B119203FFC4FCCFFD65E855FB86" blockId="4.[811,1458,503,1582]" pageId="4" pageNumber="517">
<taxonomicName id="D3EC70929203FFC4FCCFFD65EFEDFCA6" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1848" box="[835,941,758,783]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Microporidae" genus="Micropora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="4" pageNumber="517" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2698D7039203FFC4FCCFFD65EFEDFCA6" box="[835,941,758,783]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="517">Micropora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a speciose genus distributed pan-globally at the present-day. Bock (http://www.bryozoa.net/cheilostomata/ microporidae/micropora.html, accessed 
<date id="60522DD19203FFC4FB7AFCA6E921FCF9" box="[1270,1377,821,848]" pageId="4" pageNumber="517" value="2020-07-05">5/7/2020</date>
) listed a total of 70 species living and fossil, including 16 species from the Cretaceous. According to 
<bibRefCitation id="707D76E09203FFC4FB24FCE6E96AFC26" author="VOIGT E." box="[1192,1322,885,911]" pageId="4" pageNumber="517" pagination="439 - 462" refId="ref8504" refString="VOIGT E. 1981. - Repartition et utilisation stratigraphique des bryozoaires due Cretace Moyen (Aptien-Coniacien). Cretaceous Research 2: 439 - 462. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / 0195 - 6671 (81) 90033 - 1" type="journal article" year="1981">Voigt (1981</bibRefCitation>
: p. 450) the genus is recorded as far back as the Early or Middle Cenomanian but this needs to be confirmed. Putative Cretaceous species of 
<taxonomicName id="D3EC70929203FFC4FC10FC45E847FC46" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1848" box="[924,1031,982,1007]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Microporidae" genus="Micropora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="4" pageNumber="517" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2698D7039203FFC4FC10FC45E847FC46" box="[924,1031,982,1007]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="517">Micropora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have not been adequately described or illustrated, and at least some are probably not congeneric with the 
<typeStatus id="CB57B5B39203FFC4FC03FB86EFFDFB86" box="[911,957,1045,1071]" pageId="4" pageNumber="517">type</typeStatus>
species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="14530B119203FFC4FCCFFBA6E877F987" blockId="4.[811,1458,503,1582]" pageId="4" pageNumber="517">
None of the multitude of French Cretaceous bryozoans described by Alcide d’Orbigny were assigned by him to 
<taxonomicName id="D3EC70929203FFC4FCA3FBE6EFDCFB27" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1848" box="[815,924,1141,1166]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Microporidae" genus="Micropora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="4" pageNumber="517" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2698D7039203FFC4FCA3FBE6EFDCFB27" box="[815,924,1141,1166]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="517">Micropora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. A species originally assigned to 
<taxonomicName id="D3EC70929203FFC4FA95FBE7E9CDFB27" authorityName="K. Fucikova &amp; J. Kastovsky" authorityYear="2009" box="[1305,1421,1140,1166]" class="Conjugatophyceae" family="Desmidiaceae" genus="Vincularia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zygnematales" pageId="4" pageNumber="517" phylum="Charophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2698D7039203FFC4FA95FBE7E9CDFB27" box="[1305,1421,1140,1166]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="517">Vincularia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by d’Orbigny (1851: 78, pl. 657, figs 7-9) was later transferred to 
<taxonomicName id="D3EC70929203FFC4FCC6FB26EFF5FB67" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1848" box="[842,949,1205,1230]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Microporidae" genus="Micropora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="4" pageNumber="517" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2698D7039203FFC4FCC6FB26EFF5FB67" box="[842,949,1205,1230]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="517">Micropora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="707D76E09203FFC4FC52FB27E829FB66" author="VOIGT E." box="[990,1129,1204,1231]" pageId="4" pageNumber="517" pagination="1 - 45" refId="ref8421" refString="VOIGT E. 1968. - On the Cretaceous age of the so-called Jurassic cheilostomatous Polyzoa (Bryozoa). Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History) (Geology Series) 17: 1 - 45. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / p. 314178" type="journal article" year="1968">Voigt (1968)</bibRefCitation>
but this species, 
<taxonomicName id="D3EC70929203FFC4FAAFFB26E9EFFB67" baseAuthorityName="d'Orbigny" baseAuthorityYear="1851" box="[1315,1455,1205,1230]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Microporidae" genus="Micropora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="4" pageNumber="517" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="transversa">
<emphasis id="2698D7039203FFC4FAAFFB26E9EFFB67" box="[1315,1455,1205,1230]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="517">M. transversa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the Maastrichtian of Cotentin, Manche, has an erect colony-form with narrow branches and would fall outside the definition of 
<taxonomicName id="D3EC70929203FFC4FC63FA86E81CFA87" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1848" box="[1007,1116,1301,1326]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Microporidae" genus="Micropora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="4" pageNumber="517" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2698D7039203FFC4FC63FA86E81CFA87" box="[1007,1116,1301,1326]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="517">Micropora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
given by 
<bibRefCitation id="707D76E09203FFC4FB41FA87E937FA87" author="GORDON D. P." box="[1229,1399,1300,1326]" pageId="4" pageNumber="517" pagination="1 - 198" refId="ref7435" refString="GORDON D. P. 1984. - The marine fauna of New Zealand: Bryozoa: Gymnolaemata from the Kermadec Ridge. New Zealand Oceanographic Institute Memoir 91: 1 - 198." type="journal article" year="1984">Gordon (1984)</bibRefCitation>
who restricted the genus to species that have encrusting colonies. Although Voigt’s illustrations (1968: pl. 7, figs 9-12) of this species comprise photographs of poorly preserved branches, there are clear similarities with 
<taxonomicName id="D3EC70929203FFC4FBF9FA00EF9CFA67" authority="(Ducasse, 1958)" authorityName="" baseAuthorityName="Ducasse" baseAuthorityYear="1958" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Steginoporellidae" genus="Dimorphomicropora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="4" pageNumber="517" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="crestulata">
<emphasis id="2698D7039203FFC4FBF9FA00E9EEFA04" box="[1141,1454,1427,1453]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="517">Dimorphomicropora crestulata</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="707D76E09203FFC4FCB8FA20EF94FA67" author="DUCASSE J." box="[820,980,1459,1486]" pageId="4" pageNumber="517" refId="ref7196" refString="DUCASSE J. 1958. - Les Bryozoaires maestrichtiens et campaniens de la Saintonge et du Perigord occidental, repartition et valeur stratigraphique. Travaux scientifiques du Centre de Geologie Approfondie, Universite de Bordeaux, 168 p." type="book" year="1958">Ducasse, 1958</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
described below. The 
<typeStatus id="CB57B5B39203FFC4FB45FA20E96BFA64" box="[1225,1323,1459,1485]" pageId="4" pageNumber="517">lectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="D3EC70929203FFC4FAC1FA27EF22FA44" baseAuthorityName="d'Orbigny" baseAuthorityYear="1851" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Microporidae" genus="Micropora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="4" pageNumber="517" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="transversa">
<emphasis id="2698D7039203FFC4FAC1FA27EF22FA44" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="517">M. transversa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(MNHN.F. 
<accessionNumber id="0BBF96F29203FFC4FC65FA40E808FA44" box="[1001,1096,1491,1517]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/R61499" pageId="4" pageNumber="517">R61499</accessionNumber>
) is also poorly preserved but is consistent with possible synonymy between this species and 
<taxonomicName id="D3EC70929203FFC4FCA1F987EFF0F984" authorityName="" baseAuthorityName="Ducasse" baseAuthorityYear="1958" box="[813,944,1555,1581]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Steginoporellidae" genus="Dimorphomicropora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="4" pageNumber="517" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="crestulata">
<emphasis id="2698D7039203FFC4FCA1F987EFF0F984" box="[813,944,1555,1581]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="517">D. crestulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see below).
</paragraph>
